ap","i-mdi-file-edit-outline","\u002Fdocs\u002Fweb\u002Ftiptap","1.docs\u002Fweb\u002Ftiptap",[504],{"title":505,"path":506,"stem":507},"Snippets","\u002Fdocs\u002Fweb\u002Ftiptap\u002Fsnippets","1.docs\u002Fweb\u002Ftiptap\u002Fsnippets",{"id":509,"title":185,"body":510,"description":516,"extension":1561,"meta":1562,"navigation":1563,"path":186,"seo":1564,"stem":187,"__hash__":1565},"docs\u002F1.docs\u002Fkubernetes\u002Fmonitoring\u002Fcomponents.md",{"type":511,"value":512,"toc":1531},"minimark",[513,517,522,526,599,602,668,671,732,735,746,790,794,801,804,810,814,819,823,827,888,891,936,940,943,946,969,973,977,983,986,992,996,999,1003,1010,1034,1037,1082,1086,1090,1099,1155,1158,1188,1192,1196,1353,1357,1478,1482,1504,1507,1527],[514,515,516],"p",{},"Infrastructure\u002F Cluster components should be monitored separately from your applications.\nThis allows you to \"kill\" the application Prometheus in case you have screwed up in some way (e.g., messed up application metrics causing to have a billion labeled metrics).",[518,519,521],"h2",{"id":520},"master-components","Master Components",[523,524,525],"h3",{"id":525},"etcd",[527,528,529,533,540,546,585],"ul",{},[530,531,532],"li",{},"Summary: \"Why do my kubectl commands take so long?\"",[530,534,535,536],{},"Port: ",[537,538,539],"code",{},"2379\u002FTCP",[530,541,542,543],{},"Path: ",[537,544,545],{},"\u002Fmetrics",[530,547,548,549],{},"Auth: Client Certificate\n",[527,550,551],{},[530,552,553,554],{},"Notes:\n",[527,555,556,559,562,577],{},[530,557,558],{},"Thanks to etcd having a role concept, can be a \"separate\" user with just metrics access.",[530,560,561],{},"Additionally one might want to run a Kubernetes authenticated OAuth proxy in front of th etcd so that the (one or more) Prometheus can be granted access to it by RoleBinding a Role to the ServiceAccount.",[530,563,564,565,568],{},"E.g., you can create a Secret with the ETCD certificate and key using the ",[537,566,567],{},"kubectl create secret generic --from-file=...\u002Fca.crt --from-file=...\u002Fmonitoring.crt  --from-file=...\u002Fmonitoring.key",[527,569,570],{},[530,571,572,573,576],{},"Be sure to mount that Secret inside your Prometheus instance and adjust the path(s) according to the ",[537,574,575],{},"mountPath",".",[530,578,579,580,576],{},"Prometheus Config Scrape Job Reference, see ",[581,582,584],"a",{"href":583},"#prometheus-etcd-scrape-job","References Prometheus Kubernetes ETCD Scrape Job Config",[530,586,587,588],{},"What can the Metrics tell us:\n",[527,589,590,593,596],{},[530,591,592],{},"ETCD disk write latencies (they should be low, very low).",[530,594,595],{},"ETCD Quorum status as well (+ some other metrics, e.g., how many requests\u002F streams).",[530,597,598],{},"Golang Process information (e.g., CPU, memory, GC status).",[523,600,601],{"id":601},"kube-apiserver",[527,603,604,606,612,616,638],{},[530,605,532],{},[530,607,535,608,611],{},[537,609,610],{},"6443\u002FTCP"," (depends on your installation)",[530,613,542,614],{},[537,615,545],{},[530,617,618,619],{},"Auth: ServiceAccount token.\n",[527,620,621],{},[530,622,623,624],{},"Note(s):\n",[527,625,626],{},[530,627,628,629,633,634,576],{},"RBAC ClusterRole needed, see ",[581,630,632],{"href":631},"#prometheus-clusterrole","References Prometheus ClusterRole"," and ",[581,635,637],{"href":636},"#prometheus-per-namespace-role","References Prometheus Per-Namespace Role",[530,639,587,640],{},[527,641,642,654,657,660,663,666],{},[530,643,644,645],{},"API Request latencies (kubectl, operators, scheduler, controller, etc).\n",[527,646,647],{},[530,648,649,650,653],{},"Best used with ",[537,651,652],{},"histogram_quantile()"," Prometheus func over some time.",[530,655,656],{},"Admission step and webhook controller durations and latencies.",[530,658,659],{},"ETCD request metrics.",[530,661,662],{},"API server cache metrics.",[530,664,665],{},"Kubernetes API Rest Client latency, requests and duration metrics (own requests made).",[530,667,598],{},[523,669,670],{"id":670},"kube-scheduler",[527,672,673,676,681,685,710],{},[530,674,675],{},"Summary: \"How long do my Pods take to be scheudled?\" (Hints at \"you need to change your scheduler config\")",[530,677,535,678,611],{},[537,679,680],{},"443\u002FTCP",[530,682,542,683],{},[537,684,545],{},[530,686,618,687],{},[527,688,689],{},[530,690,623,691],{},[527,692,693,699],{},[530,694,628,695,633,697,576],{},[581,696,632],{"href":631},[581,698,637],{"href":636},[530,700,701,702,705,706,709],{},"The kube-scheduler needs to either listen on ",[537,703,704],{},"::"," (",[537,707,708],{},"0.0.0.0",") or have a proxy which is available to Prometheus for scraping running.",[530,711,587,712],{},[527,713,714,721,724,727,730],{},[530,715,716,717,720],{},"\"How long do my Pods take to be scheudled?\" (",[537,718,719],{},"scheduler_binding_*",")",[530,722,723],{},"Pod Preemption Algorithm latencies and more.",[530,725,726],{},"Volume scheduling duration.",[530,728,729],{},"Kubernetes API Rest Client latency, requests and duration metrics (own requests made to the API).",[530,731,598],{},[523,733,734],{"id":734},"kube-controller-manager",[736,737,739],"callout",{"icon":738},"i-ph-lightbulb-filament",[514,740,741,745],{},[742,743,744],"strong",{},"Info",":\nIf the cloud controller is used, it should also be monitored\u002F scraped for metrics.",[527,747,748,750,754,758,779],{},[530,749,675],{},[530,751,535,752,611],{},[537,753,680],{},[530,755,542,756],{},[537,757,545],{},[530,759,618,760],{},[527,761,762],{},[530,763,623,764],{},[527,765,766,772],{},[530,767,628,768,633,770,576],{},[581,769,632],{"href":631},[581,771,637],{"href":636},[530,773,774,775,705,777,709],{},"The kube-controller-manager needs to either listen on ",[537,776,704],{},[537,778,708],{},[530,780,587,781],{},[527,782,783,786,788],{},[530,784,785],{},"Work queue item count and duration, and lease holder status.",[530,787,729],{},[530,789,598],{},[523,791,793],{"id":792},"kubelet-cadvisor","kubelet (+ cadvisor)",[514,795,796,797,576],{},"See ",[581,798,800],{"href":799},"#kubelet-cadvisor-1","Node Components - kubelet",[523,802,803],{"id":803},"kube-proxy",[514,805,796,806,576],{},[581,807,809],{"href":808},"#kube-proxy-1","Node Components - kube-proxy",[523,811,813],{"id":812},"sdn-eg-calico-cilium","SDN (e.g., Calico, Cilium)",[514,815,796,816,576],{},[581,817,809],{"href":818},"#sdn-e-g-calico-cilium-1",[518,820,822],{"id":821},"node-components","Node Components",[523,824,826],{"id":825},"kubelet-cadvisor-1","kubelet (+ \"cadvisor\")",[527,828,829,831,835,839,862],{},[530,830,675],{},[530,832,535,833,611],{},[537,834,680],{},[530,836,542,837],{},[537,838,545],{},[530,840,618,841],{},[527,842,843],{},[530,844,623,845],{},[527,846,847,853],{},[530,848,628,849,633,851,576],{},[581,850,632],{"href":631},[581,852,637],{"href":636},[530,854,855,856,633,859,576],{},"kubelet needs to have the following flags active: ",[537,857,858],{},"--authorization-mode=Webhook",[537,860,861],{},"--authentication-token-webhook=true",[530,863,587,864],{},[527,865,866,872,875,881,884,886],{},[530,867,868,871],{},[537,869,870],{},"kubelet_node_config_error"," good to know if the latest config works.",[530,873,874],{},"Kubelet PLEG (\"container runtime status\") metrics.",[530,876,877,878,880],{},"\"Pod Start times\" (use ",[537,879,652],{},").",[530,882,883],{},"CGroup metrics of containers (cpu, memory, network) with Namespace and Pod labels.",[530,885,729],{},[530,887,598],{},[523,889,803],{"id":890},"kube-proxy-1",[527,892,893,895,900,904,918],{},[530,894,675],{},[530,896,535,897,611],{},[537,898,899],{},"10250\u002FTCP",[530,901,542,902],{},[537,903,545],{},[530,905,618,906],{},[527,907,908],{},[530,909,623,910],{},[527,911,912],{},[530,913,628,914,633,916,576],{},[581,915,632],{"href":631},[581,917,637],{"href":636},[530,919,587,920],{},[527,921,922,932,934],{},[530,923,924,927,928,931],{},[537,925,926],{},"iptables"," and\u002F or ",[537,929,930],{},"ipvs"," sync information (~= how long does it take for Service changes to be reflected in the \"routing\" rules).",[530,933,729],{},[530,935,598],{},[523,937,939],{"id":938},"sdn-cni-eg-calico-cilium","SDN\u002F CNI (e.g., Calico, Cilium)",[514,941,942],{},"Depends on the SDN\u002F CNI used, if there are metrics available. Calico for example can expose metrics, but that must be enabled through a environemnt variable on the Calico Node DaemonSet.",[514,944,945],{},"For other SDNs, e.g., OpenVSwitch you may need to use an \"external\" exporter when available:",[527,947,948,955,961],{},[530,949,950],{},[581,951,952],{"href":952,"rel":953},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fdigitalocean\u002Fopenvswitch_exporter",[954],"nofollow",[530,956,957],{},[581,958,959],{"href":959,"rel":960},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fovnworks\u002Fovn_exporter",[954],[530,962,963,964],{},"What can the Metrics tell us:",[527,965,966],{},[530,967,968],{},"Depending on the exporter, at least how much traffic is flowing and\u002F or if there are issues with the daemon.",[523,970,972],{"id":971},"the-nodes-themself","The Nodes themself",[974,975,976],"h4",{"id":976},"node_exporter",[514,978,796,979,576],{},[581,980,982],{"href":981},"..\u002F..\u002Fmonitoring\u002Fprometheus\u002Fexporters\u002Fnode_exporter","Monitoring\u002FPrometheus\u002FExporters - node_exporter",[974,984,985],{"id":985},"ethtool_exporter",[514,987,796,988,576],{},[581,989,991],{"href":990},"..\u002F..\u002Fmonitoring\u002Fprometheus\u002Fexporters\u002Fethtool_exporter","Monitoring\u002FPrometheus\u002FExporters - ethtool_exporter",[518,993,995],{"id":994},"additional-in-cluster-components","Additional In-Cluster Components",[514,997,998],{},"Other components that are in and\u002F or around a Kubernetes cluster.",[523,1000,1002],{"id":1001},"metrics-server-previously-named-heapster","metrics-server (previously named heapster)",[514,1004,1005,1006,720],{},"(More information ",[581,1007,1008],{"href":1008,"rel":1009},"https:\u002F\u002Fkubernetes.io\u002Fdocs\u002Ftasks\u002Fdebug-application-cluster\u002Fresource-metrics-pipeline\u002F",[954],[527,1011,1012,1014,1018,1022,1025],{},[530,1013,675],{},[530,1015,535,1016],{},[537,1017,680],{},[530,1019,542,1020],{},[537,1021,545],{},[530,1023,1024],{},"Auth: None. (Recommendation: Add Kubernetes OAuth Proxy in front)",[530,1026,587,1027],{},[527,1028,1029,1032],{},[530,1030,1031],{},"Possibly metrics on how",[530,1033,598],{},[523,1035,1036],{"id":1036},"kube-state-metrics",[527,1038,1039,1041,1051,1055,1069],{},[530,1040,675],{},[530,1042,535,1043,1046,1047,1050],{},[537,1044,1045],{},"8080\u002FTCP"," for \"cluster\" metrics and ",[537,1048,1049],{},"8081\u002FTCP"," for kube-state-metrics metrics. (Recommended to scrape both)",[530,1052,542,1053],{},[537,1054,545],{},[530,1056,618,1057],{},[527,1058,1059],{},[530,1060,623,1061],{},[527,1062,1063],{},[530,1064,628,1065,633,1067,576],{},[581,1066,632],{"href":631},[581,1068,637],{"href":636},[530,1070,587,1071],{},[527,1072,1073,1080],{},[530,1074,1075,1076,1079],{},"Metrics about Deployments, StatefulSets, Jobs, CronJobs, and basically any other objects ",[537,1077,1078],{},"Status"," (that is in the official Kubernetes APIs).",[530,1081,598],{},[518,1083,1085],{"id":1084},"other-components","Other Components",[523,1087,1089],{"id":1088},"elasticsearch","Elasticsearch",[514,1091,1092,1093,1098],{},"Elasticsearch is not providing Prometheus metrics itself, but there is a well written exporter ",[581,1094,1097],{"href":1095,"rel":1096},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fjustwatchcom\u002Felasticsearch_exporter",[954],"GitHub justwatchcom\u002Felasticsearch_exporter",".\n(There are some other exporters also available, though I have used mainly used this one for the amount of metrics I'm able to get from Elasticsearch with it)",[527,1100,1101,1104,1109,1113,1128],{},[530,1102,1103],{},"Summary: \"Is my Elasticsearch able to ingest the amount of logs? Do I need to add more data nodes and\u002F or resources?\"",[5